HEADWORD: Triticin
<hw>Trit"i*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A carbohydrate isomeric with dextrin, obtained from quitch grass
(<spn>Agropyrum repens</spn>, formerly <spn>Triticum repens</spn>) as a
white amorphous substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

